A mortality study of patients with Itai-itai disease.

Kawano S, Nakagawa H, Okumura Y, Tsujikawa K.

A follow-up study was carried out from April 1967 to October 1982 on 117 
patients with Itai-itai disease and 117 controls matched for age, sex, and 
residential area. The number of deaths during this period was significantly 
higher in the patients with Itai-itai disease (85, 72.6%) than in the controls 
