extension had a statistically insignificant influence on the survival of 
patients. In fact the 2-year survival rates of patients with caval thrombus at 
the level of the renal veins, below the large hepatic veins and above the large 
hepatic veins were 30, 36 and 32%, respectively. Our statistical data 
demonstrate that caval involvement has a very negative impact on the prognosis 
of patients with renal cancer.

